result.execSummary:
The defendant Austin M Belling was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manufacture/Deliver Heroin (<3g) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(d)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: Conditions of extended supervision are the same as those outlined for probation.

miscConds.notes: Buy Money due as $40 joint & several; $50 sole obligation. Cash bond on file shall be applied to amounts due. If probation is revoked or will discharge with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.

Defendant shall not possess or consume alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia without a valid prescription. 
Defendant shall not enter any establishment where the primary purpose is the sale or service of alcohol. 
Defendant shall not have direct or indirect contact with Ashley S. or Tiffany R.

Defendant shall participate in an AODA assessment and all counseling or treatment programs as directed by his supervising agent. 
Defendant shall pay Dept of Corrections supervision fees.
Defendant shall avoid places where drugs are used or sold. 
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample. 
Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.
Defendant shall obtain and maintain full time employment or school or a combination thereof. 
Defendant shall advise his supervising agent within 48 hours of being prescribed medications.
Defendant shall notify his health care providers of his addiction history.

timeConds.notes:
With Huber privileges consistent with the rules of the jail while the inmate maintains a minimum security status. The defendant, at the discretion of the Sheriff, may perform community service work as an inmate worker in the county jail and shall earn statutory good time for same.
First six months to be served up front. Remaining six months is stayed and may be imposed at the probation agent's discretion. Probation agent may lift the stay on the remaining six months condition time at any time, including forthwith.
